						               													<description>sQuizz is a fast trivia game where all players participate the whole time and all players stand a fair chance of winning.&amp;#10;In each round the players have to find the minimum, middle, or maximum value of the three options on the question card.&amp;#10;Example: The reader rolls the dice which lands on two, meaning that the other players must identify which of the answers is the middle answer. The reader reads: &amp;ldquo;Age &amp;ndash; A: Yoda, B: Papa Smurf, C: Noah&amp;rdquo;. In this example the middle answer was Yoda (with 900 years against Papa Smurf at 542 and Noah at 950 years).&amp;#10;Each player secretly gives his answer using one of his answer tokens. Also, each player secretly places a betting chip (value 1-8). Each bet can only be used once. Wrong bets are put aside; right bets are placed at the center of the table without revealing the value.&amp;#10;When all betting chips have been used, the total value for each player&amp;rsquo;s chips (unique colors) is counted and the player with the highest score wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
